    int[] intArray = { 5, 7, 9};
    oracle.sql.ArrayDescriptor aDescriptor = new oracle.sql.ArrayDescriptor(&quot;&lt;user&gt;.TYPE1&quot;, connection);
    oracle.sql.ARRAY array = new oracle.sql.ARRAY(aDescriptor, connection, intArray);
    
    Should be changed to:
    
    int[] intArray = { 5, 7, 9};
    java.sql.Array array = (OracleConnection)connection.createOracleArray(&quot;&lt;user&gt;.TYPE1&quot;, intArray);

&gt; NOTE:Oracle does not support anonymous array types and so does not
&gt; support the standard Connection.createArrayOf method.

I&#39;d say the reason is that PL/SQL is inspired by ADA and ADA is strongly typed language. Oracle does not have generic type for array of Strings, users have to create a named type for each use of non-scalar type.

