I stumbled upon the same _weird_ behaviour and decided to fix it by reimplementing the functionality (in kotlin, converting to java should be easy).

Background: Some libraries (postgres-jdbc in particular) uses a code-block like this to copy data:

```kotlin
val buf = ByteArray(8192)
while (true) {
  val len = stream.read(buf, 0, 8192) 
  // do something with the len bytes

  if (len &lt; 8192) {
    // nothing more to read
    break
  }
}
```

So, here is the _correct_ implementation:

```kotlin
package de.elektrowolle.commons.kotlin.streams

import java.io.InputStream


/** Reimplementation of java.io.SequenceInputStream with _correct_ implementation of available(), skip() and read(byte[], int, int)
 * @see java.io.SequenceInputStream
 */
class SequenceInputStream(
    private val stream1: InputStream,
    private val stream2: InputStream
) : InputStream() {

    override fun close() {
        // close both streams. If one fails, the other one is still closed
        // first stream1 is closed
        stream2.use { stream1.use {} }
    }

    override fun read(): Int {
        val charFromStream = stream1.read()
        return if (charFromStream != -1) charFromStream else stream2.read()
    }

    override fun available(): Int {
        return stream1.available() + stream2.available()
    }

    override fun skip(n: Long): Long {
        val skippedBytesFromFirstStream = stream1.skip(n)
        return skippedBytesFromFirstStream + stream2.skip(n - skippedBytesFromFirstStream)
    }

    override fun read(b: ByteArray, off: Int, len: Int): Int {
        // first read len bytes from s1, then read the remaining bytes from s2
        val bytesReadFromFirstStream = stream1.read(b, off, len)
        if (bytesReadFromFirstStream == -1) {
            // nothing read from first stream, read from second stream
            return stream2.read(b, off, len)
        }
        // some bytes read from first stream, read remaining bytes from second stream
        return bytesReadFromFirstStream + stream2.read(
            b,
            off + bytesReadFromFirstStream,
            len - bytesReadFromFirstStream
        )
    }
}
```

